<br>
i like FF8 over FF7 (because FF8 is basically just the upgrade to it) I re-finished FF7 after beating FF8 twice.<br>
<br>
FF8 overall had a better and more involving story line, which is confusing at first, but gets clearer when you get near the end.<br>
<br>
I think the main reason why people like FF7 is the impression it did on the big graphical change from FF6.  FF8 and FF9 was just small enhancements from FF7 so it didn't give as big of an impression as FF7 did.  Blinding people from the gameplay changes that made FF8 and FF9 better than FF7.<br>
<br>
as far as the 'old' final fantasy games, like i said. I think FF2 is the best, even though i faintly rember what FF4 and FF6 was like.<br>
<br>
You might argue that FF8 was too easy when you learn to use Limit Breaks.  But then again, Knights of the Round table just did SICK damage and made most boss encounters trivial.<br>
